```python
# The sequence below relies entirely on keystrokes, so it works even if
# window positions differ from machine to machine.
# Prerequisites:
#   • Windows OS
#   • The .pptx file you want to convert sits in C:\Slides\presentation.pptx
#   • PowerShell is available (default on Windows 10/11)
#
# Strategy:
#   1. Open the Windows “Run” dialog (Win + R).
#   2. Launch a one-liner PowerShell command that:
#        - treats the .pptx as a normal zip archive
#        - expands it into a sibling “_images” folder
#        - the images will be inside “…\ppt\media”
#
# The command is:
#   powershell -command "Expand-Archive -LiteralPath 'C:\Slides\presentation.pptx' -DestinationPath 'C:\Slides\presentation_images' -Force"

start
# 1) Open the Windows Run dialog
hot_key('win', 'r')

# 2) Type the PowerShell one-liner that extracts the images
type_text("powershell -command \"Expand-Archive -LiteralPath 'C:\\Slides\\presentation.pptx' -DestinationPath 'C:\\Slides\\presentation_images' -Force\"")

# 3) Execute the command
hot_key('enter')
end
```